HEADWORD: Carnifex
<hw>Car"ni*fex</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>caro</ets>, <ets>carnis</ets>, flesh + <ets>facere</ets> to
make.]</ety> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>The public executioner at Rome,
who executed persons of the lowest rank; hence, an executioner or
hangman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carnification</ent>⟦br⟧
